features: 😊Fun & Cute Designs: Our pacifiers are cute, comfortable, and effective at soothing and aiding in the reduction of snoring during sleep. Have fun, look good, and sleep deeper with our Littletude pacifiers.

😊Comfy, Large Teat: The comfortable and soft teat is approximately 2 inches long x 1.2 inches wide, which is perfect for adults and may help reduce snoring, resulting in a more restful night of sleep. Wake up feeling refreshed and ready for the day!
😊Extra Large Shield: Our pacifier features some of the largest, most protective shields which measure out at 2.6 inches wide x 1.9 inches tall. It's just like a regular pacifier, but larger!

😊Quality Materials: Littletude Pacifiers are made of the highest quality, safest, and softest material. The teat is silicone and is BPA and latex free. The shield is made of high quality, durable plastic. The pacifier is designed to fit perfectly in the mouth of a grown person for a soothing, relaxing experience.

😊Calm Down & Reduce Snoring: Two of the great benefits of using a pacifier are that a pacifier can help calm you down and relax you. Plus, if used when going to sleep, it may help you achieve a deeper, more restful night of sleep as it reduces snoring by keeping the tongue in the proper place in the mouth during sleep. It also encourages nasal breathing which has been shown to deliver more oxygen to the lungs and help with achieving quality sleep.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect for any ABDL or adults who have emotional needs
reviews.reviewText: I'm ABDL so pacifiers are a must for me and I only had one that I purchased several years ago and wanted more. My girlfriend had an emotional stressor that triggered a thumb-sucking behavior, so I bought this 4 pack. I gave my GF one and kept two, giving the fourth to my wife because she wanted one too. My GF hasn't sucked her thumb since she got her pacifier and I have spares now, one I clip to my sheet for sleeping, and another just in case I need it (my original one is clipped to my daily onesie).

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 10, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Love ‘em, but be careful with the handle (don’t pull it extremely hard)
reviews.reviewText: I like these binkis, the teat is a bit tough. It’s not extremely soft like some other pacis. It’s good if you like to chew it cuz it won’t pop. But be careful, I pulled the back of it hard one time tryna be all cute taking it out (the teat was in between my teeth) and the back with the little handle snapped off. I was able to put it back together, but I have to be gentle with it, cuz if I’m rough the back will pop off. None of the other ones broke, cuz now I know not to tug them really hard. But yeah, I love ‘em, I fall asleep with them in my mouth all the time :)
